			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Not to get off the subject, but I see this alot &quot;No two poison dots stack&quot;;. That is ENTIRELY UNTRUE! You can stack ALL of the shaman poison DoTs. However, in doing so, you have to cast them in the right order. Yes, It is NO LIE! I do it all the freakin time, and it does max damage!!!! Cast Ebolt, then Vemom of The Snake, Then Ebreath, and watch it freakin wither away!<BR>
<BR>
Oh, and top of that, you can stack a disease DoT in there. I have yet to try and stack multiple disease. The reason being is that usually, with the combination listed above, I either cannot afford it mana wise, or do not need it.<BR>
<BR>
I am not saying that &quot;shamans are better than necro's&quot; or vice/versa. What I am saying is that its not the class that determines the uber char. Its knowing how to properly utilize your character and his/her resources.<BR>
<BR>
Of course, I can also make a few observations (that are entirely stereotypical and inappropriate)  about your average necro.<BR>
<BR>
1. Necro's hardly ever group. They wouldnt even join a group if asked (not all necro's, but most). Thus, they usually do not care what others think of them. Many a necro accused of KS have the typical response: &quot;so?&quot;<BR>
<BR>
2. Necro's hardly ever go into dungeons. There is no room for them to solo nor fear kite. usually, a necro will log and use his/her Iksar Monk to Solo in dungeons (yes, I dared go there). This is done to get Phat Dungeon Lewt for the necro ;).<BR>
<BR>
3. Despite PvP, Necros want to be left alone. If there where a single player version of this game, then you would see hardly ANY necros on the blue servers.<BR>
<BR>
Just mt 2 gp's worth ;)<BR>
<BR>
<BR>

